Two international fishing industry groups have called for limits on tuna catches to prevent overfishing.
An international commission reduced the gross catch of bluefin tuna, leading to import concerns in Japan.
The meeting in Kobe aims to address the declining tuna stocks and establish a moratorium on large tuna vessels.
Environmentalists urge a radical change in fishing practices to save tuna populations.
The conference seeks to implement a global action plan, including tracking systems and certificates of origin.
Participants emphasize sustainable management of tuna resources to prevent further decline and extinction, highlighting the urgent need for conservation efforts.
